			<span class="anthracite size13" contentbodystyle="Anthracite">You said it all with:



"Who throws surveillance on a previous employer like this? The ex-employee has all the cards."



To me, it would seem that the ex-employee is more likely privy to info of some sort that the client doesn't want public ... a whistleblower? ... and is surreptitiously bringing you on-board to find out what/how much and get your assistance to prevent any legal ramifications for himself and his company.



The laptop may be the method the ex-employee is using to prove the case?</span>
